The paper addresses the problem of searching for semantically similar images, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed approach involves learning a discriminative subspace and quantizing the data points, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper also mentions the formulation of the problem as a classification task, which is a common theme in natural language processing (cs.CL).
